            <thetext>Deleting a resource file from an already scanned library will lead to a runtime 
exception where the generator tries to copy the deleted file (e.g. during 
build-resources job).

The issue is that the resource file has been registerd on a previous run, and 
that this knowledge is cached. The library is re-scanned ok on change, but the 
old collection of resources is not reset.</thetext>
